06/04/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbia-Montenegro Defence Minister Zoran Stankovic and US Ambassador to Belgrade Michael Polt sealed an agreement Wednesday (5 April) on preventing the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction. 
Polt said it proved the mutual desire for co-operation and would strengthen bilateral ties in the defence and military sectors. 
As soon as the Serbian Parliament ratifies the agreement, Washington will provide over $800,000 for border control training. 
(Tanjug, RTS, UPI - 05/04/06)
